      "lesson title": "AI in Advertising: Truth, Bias, and Manipulation",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Advertising has always relied on persuasion, but artificial intelligence is transforming the scale and sophistication of how audiences are targeted and influenced. This lesson explores the ethical risks that arise when AI is used to craft messages, personalise content, and reach specific groups of people with pinpoint accuracy. You will learn how algorithmic bias can creep into advertising systems, leading to unfair or discriminatory outcomes that may go unnoticed by the brands responsible. We will also examine how AI-powered tools can blur the line between helpful personalisation and manipulative tactics that exploit human psychology. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of what responsible, transparent advertising looks like in an age where AI is doing much of the work behind the scenes.",
